Question 3.1.6:

Maximize f(x_i)=(x_1^a_1)*(x_2^a_2)*...*(x_n^a_n)

subject to: sum_1_n [x_i] = 1

The function looks multinomial and Lagrangian. 

Lagrangian: lambda = 1-sum_1_n [x_i]

The function under additional constraints:

  f(x_i) = Π*(x_i^a_i) + lambda*[1-sum_1_n [x_i]]

A derivative with the constraint term:
 
  df(x_i)/dx_i = d/dx_i[Π*(x_i^a_i) + lambda*[1-sum_1_n [x_i]]

               = 0

  df(x_i)/dx_i = lambda*d/dx_i[1-sum_1_n [x_i]]

        lambda = sum_1_n [a_i/x_i]

A lambda re-entry in the constraint:

  sum_1_n [x_i] = sum_1_n [a_i/lambda]
 
                = 1

         lambda = n

  sum_1_n[x_i]  = (1/n)*sum_1_n[a_i]

The average a-value maximizes the original function.



 

     



